{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884946093,"sessionID":"ses_28504be3fffeAI67laka6We2j7","part":{"id":"prt_d7afdc28a001Dgkt35ESKys7Bu","messageID":"msg_d7afdba77001uPPPwrwhgISq32","sessionID":"ses_28504be3fffeAI67laka6We2j7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b74e50e47933493dad03a111","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP ÂàÜÊûêÂô®Á§∫‰æãÂ∫îÁî® ‚Äî Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers the PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application for the AgentCube Python SDK. It demonstrates the complete workflow of file upload, remote code execution, and result download using `CodeInterpreterClient`, providing users with a runnable network analysis reference implementation.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 System Context\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê\n13: ‚îÇ                         User / Developer                             ‚îÇ\n14: ‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê    ‚îÇ\n15: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ              examples/pcap_analyzer/                         ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n16: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n17: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ              pcap_analyzer.py                         ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n18: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ         (CLI Example Script)                          ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n19: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n20: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ                         ‚îÇ                                   ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n21: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n22: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ         CodeInterpreterClient (SDK)                   ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n23: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ   (upload_file, run_code, execute_command,            ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n24: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    download_file, list_files, context manager)        ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n25: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n26: ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò    ‚îÇ\n27: ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò\n28:                              ‚îÇ\n29:                              ‚ñº\n30: ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê\n31: ‚îÇ                    AgentCube Platform                                ‚îÇ\n32: ‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê          ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê   ‚îÇ\n33: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  Control Plane       ‚îÇ‚óÑ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫‚îÇ  Code Interpreter Pod      ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ\n34: ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  (Session Lifecycle) ‚îÇ         ‚îÇ  (Python 3.10+, scapy)     ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ\n35: ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò          ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò   ‚îÇ\n36: ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n40: \n41: - **Example-only**: No modifications to SDK core code; uses only public API (`__all__` exports)\n42: - **CLI script style**: Consistent with existing examples (`basic_usage.py`, `agent_runtime_usage.py`)\n43: - **Self-contained**: Single script with embedded analysis logic via `run_code`\n44: - **Graceful degradation**: `tshark` as optional enhancement with conditional detection\n45: - **Small footprint**: Sample PCAP < 1MB, no chunked upload complexity\n46: \n47: ### 1.4 Package Structure\n48: \n49: ```\n50: sdk-python/\n51: ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ examples/\n52: ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ basic_usage.py                      # Existing\n53: ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ agent_runtime_usage.py              # Existing\n54: ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ pcap_analyzer/                      # NEW (this AR)\n55: ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pcap_analyzer.py                # Main example script\n56: ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md                       # Usage guide\n57: ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ requirements.txt                # Example dependencies\n58: ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sample_traffic.pcap             # Sample PCAP file (< 1MB)\n59: ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n63: \n64: | Dependency | Scope | Purpose |\n65: |------------|-------|---------|\n66: | `agentcube-sdk` | Local import | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n67: | `scapy` | Remote sandbox | PCAP parsing (installed via `run_code` if needed) |\n68: | `tshark` (optional) | Remote sandbox | CLI filtering tool (conditional detection) |\n69: \n70: **No new Python package dependencies** ‚Äî the example script uses only stdlib + `agentcube-sdk`.\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 2. Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### 2.1 Analysis Result Format (JSON)\n77: \n78: The remote analysis script produces JSON output with the following structure:\n79: \n80: ```json\n81: {\n82:   \"file_name\": \"sample_traffic.pcap\",\n83:   \"total_packets\": 1234,\n84:   \"duration_seconds\": 60.5,\n85:   \"protocols\": {\n86:     \"TCP\": 800,\n87:     \"UDP\": 300,\n88:     \"ICMP\": 50,\n89:     \"HTTP\": 60,\n90:     \"DNS\": 24\n91:   },\n92:   \"top_source_ips\": [\n93:     {\"ip\": \"192.168.1.100\", \"count\": 500},\n94:     {\"ip\": \"10.0.0.1\", \"count\": 300}\n95:   ],\n96:   \"top_dest_ips\": [\n97:     {\"ip\": \"8.8.8.8\", \"count\": 200},\n98:     {\"ip\": \"1.1.1.1\", \"count\": 150}\n99:   ],\n100:   \"timeline\": [\n101:     {\"timestamp\": 1699000000.0, \"packets\": 100},\n102:     {\"timestamp\": 1699000010.0, \"packets\": 150}\n103:   ],\n104:   \"errors\": []\n105: }\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### 2.2 CLI Arguments\n109: \n110: | Argument | Type | Default | Description |\n111: |----------|------|---------|-------------|\n112: | `--pcap-file` | `str` | `sample_traffic.pcap` | Path to PCAP file to analyze |\n113: | `--output` | `str` | `analysis_result.json` | Local path for result output |\n114: | `--top-n` | `int` | `10` | Number of top IPs to report |\n115: | `--timeline-interval` | `float` | `10.0` | Timeline bucket size in seconds |\n116: | `--verbose` | `flag` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n117: \n118: ### 2.3 Environment Variables\n119: \n120: | Variable | Required | Description |\n121: |----------|----------|-------------|\n122: | `ROUTER_URL` | Yes | Router endpoint URL |\n123: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | No | Control plane URL (defaults to SDK default) |\n124: | `AUTH_TOKEN` | No | Auth token (falls back to SA token file) |\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 3. Interfaces\n129: \n130: ### 3.1 Main Script Entry Point\n131: \n132: ```python\n133: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n134: \"\"\"PCAP Analyzer Example ‚Äî demonstrates CodeInterpreterClient workflow.\"\"\"\n135: \n136: import argparse\n137: import json\n138: import os\n139: import sys\n140: \n141: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n142: \n143: \n144: def main():\n145:     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"PCAP Analyzer Example\")\n146:     parser.add_argument(\"--pcap-file\", default=\"sample_traffic.pcap\")\n147:     parser.add_argument(\"--output\", default=\"analysis_result.json\")\n148:     parser.add_argument(\"--top-n\", type=int, default=10)\n149:     parser.add_argument(\"--timeline-interval\", type=float, default=10.0)\n150:     parser.add_argument(\"--verbose\", action=\"store_true\")\n151:     args = parser.parse_args()\n152: \n153:     router_url = os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n154:     if not router_url:\n155:         print(\"Error: ROUTER_URL environment variable is required\", file=sys.stderr)\n156:         sys.exit(1)\n157: \n158:     analyze_pcap(\n159:         pcap_file=args.pcap_file,\n160:         output_file=args.output,\n161:         top_n=args.top_n,\n162:         timeline_interval=args.timeline_interval,\n163:         verbose=args.verbose,\n164:         router_url=router_url,\n165:     )\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### 3.2 Core Analysis Function\n169: \n170: ```python\n171: def analyze_pcap(\n172:     pcap_file: str,\n173:     output_file: str,\n174:     top_n: int,\n175:     timeline_interval: float,\n176:     verbose: bool,\n177:     router_url: str,\n178: ) -> None:\n179:     \"\"\"Upload PCAP, run analysis, download results.\"\"\"\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Workflow:**\n183: \n184: 1. Validate PCAP file exists locally\n185: 2. Create `CodeInterpreterClient` (context manager)\n186: 3. Upload PCAP file to remote sandbox (`upload_file`)\n187: 4. Install `scapy` if needed (`run_code` with `pip install`)\n188: 5. Execute analysis script (`run_code` with embedded Python)\n189: 6. Optionally run `tshark` commands (`execute_command` if available)\n190: 7. Write results to remote file (`write_file` or script output)\n191: 8. Download results (`download_file`)\n192: 9. Print summary to console\n193: 10. Context manager cleanup (`__exit__` ‚Üí `stop()`)\n194: \n195: ### 3.3 Embedded Analysis Script (via `run_code`)\n196: \n197: The analysis logic is passed as a Python string to `run_code`. It uses `scapy` to parse the PCAP file:\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: ANALYSIS_SCRIPT = \"\"\"\n201: from scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, Raw\n202: import json\n203: import sys\n204: from collections import Counter\n205: \n206: def analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n=10, timeline_interval=10.0):\n207:     packets = rdpcap(pcap_path)\n208:     \n209:     result = {\n210:         \"file_name\": pcap_path,\n211:         \"total_packets\": len(packets),\n212:         \"duration_seconds\": 0.0,\n213:         \"protocols\": {},\n214:         \"top_source_ips\": [],\n215:         \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n216:         \"timeline\": [],\n217:         \"errors\": []\n218:     }\n219:     \n220:     if not packets:\n221:         return result\n222:     \n223:     # Duration\n224:     first_ts = float(packets[0].time)\n225:     last_ts = float(packets[-1].time)\n226:     result[\"duration_seconds\"] = last_ts - first_ts\n227:     \n228:     # Protocol distribution\n229:     proto_counts = Counter()\n230:     src_ips = Counter()\n231:     dst_ips = Counter()\n232:     timeline_buckets = Counter()\n233:     \n234:     for pkt in packets:\n235:         ts = float(pkt.time)\n236:         bucket = int((ts - first_ts) / timeline_interval) * timeline_interval + first_ts\n237:         \n238:         if pkt.haslayer(TCP):\n239:             proto_counts[\"TCP\"] += 1\n240:             if pkt.haslayer(Raw):\n241:                 proto_counts[\"HTTP\"] += 1  # Simplified HTTP detection\n242:         elif pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n243:             if pkt.haslayer(DNS):\n244:                 proto_counts[\"DNS\"] += 1\n245:             else:\n246:                 proto_counts[\"UDP\"] += 1\n247:         elif pkt.haslayer(ICMP):\n248:             proto_counts[\"ICMP\"] += 1\n249:         else:\n250:             proto_counts[\"Other\"] += 1\n251:         \n252:         if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n253:             src_ips[pkt[IP].src] += 1\n254:             dst_ips[pkt[IP].dst] += 1\n255:         \n256:         timeline_buckets[bucket] += 1\n257:     \n258:     result[\"protocols\"] = dict(proto_counts)\n259:     result[\"top_source_ips\"] = [\n260:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n261:         for ip, count in src_ips.most_common(top_n)\n262:     ]\n263:     result[\"top_dest_ips\"] = [\n264:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n265:         for ip, count in dst_ips.most_common(top_n)\n266:     ]\n267:     result[\"timeline\"] = sorted([\n268:         {\"timestamp\": ts, \"packets\": count}\n269:         for ts, count in timeline_buckets.items()\n270:     ], key=lambda x: x[\"timestamp\"])\n271:     \n272:     return result\n273: \n274: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n275:     pcap_file = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else \"/tmp/uploaded.pcap\"\n276:     top_n = int(sys.argv[2]) if len(sys.argv) > 2 else 10\n277:     interval = float(sys.argv[3]) if len(sys.argv) > 3 else 10.0\n278:     \n279:     result = analyze_pcap(pcap_file, top_n, interval)\n280:     print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n281: \"\"\"\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### 3.4 Optional tshark Enhancement\n285: \n286: ```python\n287: def check_tshark_available(client: CodeInterpreterClient) -> bool:\n288:     \"\"\"Check if tshark is available in the remote sandbox.\"\"\"\n289:     try:\n290:         result = client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")\n291:         return result.strip() != \"\"\n292:     except Exception:\n293:         return False\n294: \n295: \n296: def run_tshark_filter(client: CodeInterpreterClient, pcap_path: str, filter_expr: str) -> str:\n297:     \"\"\"Run tshark with a display filter on the remote PCAP.\"\"\"\n298:     cmd = f\"tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len\"\n299:     return client.execute_command(cmd)\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## 4. Error Handling\n305: \n306: ### 4.1 Error Classification\n307: \n308: | Scenario | Exception | Handling |\n309: |----------|-----------|----------|\n310: | PCAP file not found locally | `FileNotFoundError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n311: | `ROUTER_URL` not set | `ValueError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n312: | Upload failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n313: | `scapy` installation failure | `CommandExecutionError` | Retry or warn, continue |\n314: | Analysis script error | `CommandExecutionError` | Print stderr, exit 1 |\n315: | Result download failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n316: | Invalid JSON output | `json.JSONDecodeError` | Print raw output, warn |\n317: | Context manager cleanup failure | SDK exception | Log warning, exit |\n318: \n319: ### 4.2 Error Recovery Strategy\n320: \n321: ```python\n322: def analyze_pcap(...):\n323:     # Pre-flight checks\n324:     if not os.path.exists(pcap_file):\n325:         print(f\"Error: PCAP file not found: {pcap_file}\", file=sys.stderr)\n326:         sys.exit(1)\n327:     \n328:     # Context manager ensures cleanup\n329:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n330:         name=\"pcap-analyzer\",\n331:         router_url=router_url,\n332:         verbose=verbose,\n333:     ) as client:\n334:         try:\n335:             # Upload\n336:             remote_path = f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\"\n337:             client.upload_file(pcap_file, remote_path)\n338:             \n339:             # Install scapy (best effort)\n340:             try:\n341:                 client.run_code(\"python\", \"import scapy\")\n342:             except Exception:\n343:                 if verbose:\n344:                     print(\"Installing scapy in remote sandbox...\")\n345:                 client.run_code(\"python\", \"import subprocess; subprocess.run(['pip', 'install', 'scapy'])\")\n346:             \n347:             # Run analysis\n348:             script = ANALYSIS_SCRIPT.replace(\"TOP_N_PLACEHOLDER\", str(top_n))\n349:             result_json = client.run_code(\"python\", script)\n350:             result = json.loads(result_json)\n351:             \n352:             # Optional tshark\n353:             if check_tshark_available(client):\n354:                 tshark_result = run_tshark_filter(client, remote_path, \"tcp\")\n355:                 result[\"tshark_tcp_summary\"] = tshark_result\n356:             \n357:             # Save results locally\n358:             with open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n359:                 json.dump(result, f, indent=2)\n360:             \n361:             # Print summary\n362:             print_analysis_summary(result)\n363:             \n364:         except Exception as e:\n365:             print(f\"Analysis failed: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n366:             sys.exit(1)\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## 5. Implementation Notes\n372: \n373: ### 5.1 Remote Sandbox Assumptions\n374: \n375: | Assumption | Verification | Fallback |\n376: |------------|--------------|----------|\n377: | Python 3.10+ available | `run_code(\"python\", \"import sys; print(sys.version)\")` | Error if not met |\n378: | `pip install` works | Try `pip install scapy` | Pre-install in sandbox image |\n379: | `/tmp` writable | `execute_command(\"touch /tmp/test && rm /tmp/test\")` | Use alternative path |\n380: | `tshark` available (optional) | `execute_command(\"which tshark\")` | Skip tshark features |\n381: \n382: ### 5.2 Script Size Considerations\n383: \n384: The embedded `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` is ~60 lines of Python. For `run_code`, this is passed as a string argument. If the script grows significantly, consider:\n385: \n386: 1. Using `write_file` to upload the script first, then `execute_command` to run it\n387: 2. Splitting into multiple `run_code` calls\n388: \n389: Current approach (inline) is preferred for simplicity and demonstration purposes.\n390: \n391: ### 5.3 Timeout Configuration\n392: \n393: | Operation | Timeout | Rationale |\n394: |-----------|---------|-----------|\n395: | PCAP upload | Default (120s) | < 1MB file, should be fast |\n396: | scapy install | 60s | Network-dependent |\n397: | Analysis execution | 120s | Depends on PCAP size |\n398: | tshark filter | 60s | Optional enhancement |\n399: | Result download | Default (120s) | JSON output, small |\n400: \n401: ### 5.4 Sample PCAP Generation\n402: \n403: The `sample_traffic.pcap` file can be generated using `scapy`:\n404: \n405: ```python\n406: # scripts/generate_sample_pcap.py\n407: from scapy.all import IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, wrpcap, Ether\n408: import random\n409: \n410: packets = []\n411: base_time = 1699000000.0\n412: \n413: for i in range(100):\n414:     src = f\"192.168.1.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n415:     dst = f\"10.0.0.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n416:     \n417:     if i % 3 == 0:\n418:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / TCP(sport=random.randint(1024, 65535), dport=80)\n419:     elif i % 3 == 1:\n420:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / UDP(sport=53, dport=random.randint(1024, 65535))\n421:     else:\n422:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / ICMP()\n423:     \n424:     pkt.time = base_time + i * 0.5\n425:     packets.append(pkt)\n426: \n427: wrpcap(\"sample_traffic.pcap\", packets)\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ---\n431: \n432: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n433: \n434: ### 6.1 Test Categories\n435: \n436: | Category | Scope | Approach |\n437: |----------|-------|----------|\n438: | Script validation | Syntax, imports | `python -m py_compile pcap_analyzer.py` |\n439: | Unit tests | Analysis logic | Run embedded script locally with test PCAP |\n440: | Integration tests | SDK interaction | Mock `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n441: | Manual E2E | Full workflow | Run against real AgentCube platform |\n442: \n443: ### 6.2 Key Test Scenarios\n444: \n445: | Test Name | Description |\n446: |-----------|-------------|\n447: | `test_script_syntax` | Embedded analysis script compiles without errors |\n448: | `test_analysis_with_sample_pcap` | Run analysis on sample_traffic.pcap, verify JSON structure |\n449: | `test_empty_pcap` | Handle PCAP with 0 packets gracefully |\n450: | `test_cli_argument_parsing` | Verify argparse handles all flags correctly |\n451: | `test_missing_router_url` | Exit with error if ROUTER_URL not set |\n452: | `test_missing_pcap_file` | Exit with error if PCAP file not found |\n453: | `test_mocked_sdk_workflow` | Mock CodeInterpreterClient, verify call sequence |\n454: \n455: ### 6.3 Mocked SDK Test Example\n456: \n457: ```python\n458: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n459: \n460: def test_mocked_sdk_workflow():\n461:     \"\"\"Verify the expected SDK call sequence.\"\"\"\n462:     mock_client = MagicMock()\n463:     mock_client.__enter__ = MagicMock(return_value=mock_client)\n464:     mock_client.__exit__ = MagicMock(return_value=False)\n465:     \n466:     mock_client.run_code.return_value = json.dumps({\n467:         \"total_packets\": 100,\n468:         \"protocols\": {\"TCP\": 60, \"UDP\": 40},\n469:         \"top_source_ips\": [],\n470:         \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n471:         \"timeline\": [],\n472:         \"errors\": []\n473:     })\n474:     \n475:     with patch(\"agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\", return_value=mock_client):\n476:         # Run analyze_pcap with test fixtures\n477:         # Verify call sequence:\n478:         # 1. upload_file called\n479:         # 2. run_code called for analysis\n480:         # 3. download_file or result handling\n481:         pass\n482: ```\n483: \n484: ---\n485: \n486: ## 7. Usage Examples\n487: \n488: ### 7.1 Basic Usage\n489: \n490: ```bash\n491: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n492: cd examples/pcap_analyzer\n493: python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n494: ```\n495: \n496: **Expected output:**\n497: \n498: ```\n499: PCAP Analysis Complete\n500: =====================\n501: File: sample_traffic.pcap\n502: Total packets: 100\n503: Duration: 49.50s\n504: \n505: Protocol Distribution:\n506:   TCP:  60 (60.0%)\n507:   UDP:  40 (40.0%)\n508: \n509: Top Source IPs:\n510:   192.168.1.105: 15 packets\n511:   192.168.1.200: 12 packets\n512:   192.168.1.50:  10 packets\n513: \n514: Top Destination IPs:\n515:   10.0.0.1: 25 packets\n516:   10.0.0.5: 20 packets\n517: \n518: Results saved to: analysis_result.json\n519: ```\n520: \n521: ### 7.2 Custom Parameters\n522: \n523: ```bash\n524: python pcap_analyzer.py \\\n525:   --pcap-file /path/to/capture.pcap \\\n526:   --output /path/to/report.json \\\n527:   --top-n 20 \\\n528:   --timeline-interval 5.0 \\\n529:   --verbose\n530: ```\n531: \n532: ### 7.3 With tshark (if available)\n533: \n534: When `tshark` is detected in the remote sandbox, additional filtering output is included:\n535: \n536: ```\n537: tshark TCP Filter Results:\n538:   192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1500 bytes\n539:   192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1200 bytes\n540:   ...\n541: ```\n542: \n543: ---\n544: \n545: ## 8. README Content\n546: \n547: The `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` will contain:\n548: \n549: ```markdown\n550: # PCAP Analyzer Example\n551: \n552: Demonstrates the complete CodeInterpreterClient workflow:\n553: upload ‚Üí analyze ‚Üí download.\n554: \n555: ## Prerequisites\n556: \n557: - Python 3.10+\n558: - `agentcube-sdk` installed\n559: - Access to AgentCube platform (ROUTER_URL)\n560: \n561: ## Quick Start\n562: \n563: ```bash\n564: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n565: python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n566: ```\n567: \n568: ## Analysis Features\n569: \n570: - Protocol distribution (TCP/UDP/ICMP/DNS/HTTP)\n571: - Top N source and destination IPs\n572: - Traffic timeline overview\n573: - Optional tshark filtering (if available in sandbox)\n574: \n575: ## Output\n576: \n577: Results are saved as JSON and printed as a summary to stdout.\n578: ```\n\n(End of file - total 578 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP ÂàÜÊûêÂô®Á§∫‰æãÂ∫îÁî® ‚Äî Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application for the AgentCube Python SDK. It demonstrates the complete workflow of file upload, remote code execution, and result download using `CodeInterpreterClient`, providing users with a runnable network analysis reference implementation.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\n‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê\n‚îÇ                         User / Developer                             ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê    ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ              examples/pcap_analyzer/                         ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ              pcap_analyzer.py                         ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ         (CLI Example Script)                          ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ                         ‚îÇ                                   ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T0733