{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885021992,"sessionID":"ses_28504be3fffeAI67laka6We2j7","part":{"id":"prt_d7afe31b6001MzFlybENNpigC5","messageID":"msg_d7afe213d001WiM5IPWcxOX420","sessionID":"ses_28504be3fffeAI67laka6We2j7","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_7885868b0e4743e49099d400","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-037: PCAP ÂàÜÊûêÂô®Á§∫‰æãÂ∫îÁî® ‚Äî Tasks\n\n**Module:** `example` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n**Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n\n---\n\n## T-1: Project scaffolding ‚Äî `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory structure\n\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/__init__.py` (empty, marks package)\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/requirements.txt` with `agentcube-sdk` and `scapy`\n- [ ] Verify directory structure matches design spec\n\n## T-2: CLI argument parser (`argparse`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `parse_args()` function with arguments:\n  - `--pcap-file` (str, default `sample_traffic.pcap`)\n  - `--output` (str, default `analysis_result.json`)\n  - `--top-n` (int, default `10`)\n  - `--timeline-interval` (float, default `10.0`)\n  - `--verbose` (flag, default `False`)\n- [ ] Validate `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set; print error and `sys.exit(1)` if missing\n- [ ] Write test: all arguments parsed with defaults\n- [ ] Write test: explicit arguments override defaults\n- [ ] Write test: missing `ROUTER_URL` ‚Üí error message to stderr, exit code 1\n\n## T-3: Pre-flight validation helpers\n\n- [ ] Implement `validate_pcap_file(pcap_file: str) -> None` ‚Äî raises `FileNotFoundError` if file does not exist\n- [ ] Implement `check_python_version() -> None` ‚Äî verifies Python 3.10+ via `sys.version_info`\n- [ ] Write test: valid PCAP path passes validation\n- [ ] Write test: nonexistent PCAP path raises `FileNotFoundError` with descriptive message\n- [ ] Write test: Python < 3.10 raises error\n\n## T-4: Embedded analysis script (`ANALYSIS_SCRIPT`)\n\n- [ ] Define `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` constant ‚Äî Python string using `scapy.all` (`rdpcap`, `IP`, `TCP`, `UDP`, `ICMP`, `DNS`, `Raw`)\n- [ ] Implement `analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n, timeline_interval)` function inside the script:\n  - Parse packets with `rdpcap`\n  - Calculate `duration_seconds` from first/last packet timestamps\n  - Count protocol distribution (TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, HTTP via `Raw` layer)\n  - Compute top N source/destination IPs using `collections.Counter`\n  - Build timeline buckets grouped by `timeline_interval`\n  - Return JSON-serializable dict matching design spec format\n- [ ] Handle empty PCAP (0 packets) gracefully ‚Äî return result with zero counts\n- [ ] Write test: embedded script syntax compiles (`py_compile`)\n- [ ] Write test: run embedded script locally against a test PCAP, verify JSON structure has all required keys\n\n## T-5: `check_tshark_available` helper\n\n- [ ] Implement `check_tshark_available(client: CodeInterpreterClient) -> bool`\n- [ ] Use `client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")` ‚Äî return `True` if non-empty output, `False` on exception\n- [ ] Write test: mocked client returns `True` when `which tshark` succeeds\n- [ ] Write test: mocked client returns `False` when command raises exception\n\n## T-6: `run_tshark_filter` helper\n\n- [ ] Implement `run_tshark_filter(client, pcap_path, filter_expr) -> str`\n- [ ] Construct command: `tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len`\n- [ ] Return `client.execute_command(cmd)` output\n- [ ] Write test: mocked client returns tshark output string\n\n## T-7: `print_analysis_summary` output formatter\n\n- [ ] Implement `print_analysis_summary(result: dict) -> None` that prints:\n  - Header: \"PCAP Analysis Complete\" with separator\n  - File name, total packets, duration\n  - Protocol distribution with counts and percentages\n  - Top N source IPs with packet counts\n  - Top N destination IPs with packet counts\n  - Result file path\n- [ ] Write test: captures stdout, verifies formatted output contains all sections\n- [ ] Write test: handles empty protocols dict gracefully\n\n## T-8: Core `analyze_pcap` orchestration function\n\n- [ ] Implement `analyze_pcap(pcap_file, output_file, top_n, timeline_interval, verbose, router_url) -> None`:\n  1. Validate PCAP file exists locally\n  2. Enter `CodeInterpreterClient` context manager with `name=\"pcap-analyzer\"`, `router_url`, `verbose`\n  3. Upload PCAP: `client.upload_file(pcap_file, f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\")`\n  4. Best-effort scapy install: try `import scapy`, fall back to `pip install scapy` via `run_code`\n  5. Execute analysis: `client.run_code(\"python\", ANALYSIS_SCRIPT)` with parameters\n  6. Parse JSON result from `run_code` output\n  7. If `check_tshark_available(client)`, run `run_tshark_filter` and attach to result\n  8. Write result JSON to `output_file` locally\n  9. Call `print_analysis_summary(result)`\n- [ ] Wrap in try/except ‚Äî print `Analysis failed: {e}` to stderr, `sys.exit(1)` on failure\n- [ ] Write test: mocked `CodeInterpreterClient` verifies full call sequence (upload ‚Üí run_code scapy check ‚Üí run_code analysis ‚Üí file write ‚Üí summary)\n- [ ] Write test: scapy already installed skips `pip install`\n- [ ] Write test: scapy not installed triggers `pip install`\n- [ ] Write test: tshark available ‚Üí additional `execute_command` and `run_tshark_filter` called\n- [ ] Write test: tshark not available ‚Üí skips tshark steps\n- [ ] Write test: `run_code` raises exception ‚Üí error printed, exit 1\n- [ ] Write test: context manager `__exit__` called even on exception (cleanup guarantee)\n\n## T-9: `main()` entry point\n\n- [ ] Implement `main()` function:\n  - Call `parse_args()` to get CLI arguments\n  - Resolve `ROUTER_URL` from environment\n  - Call `analyze_pcap()` with parsed args and router URL\n- [ ] Add `if __name__ == \"__main__\": main()` guard\n- [ ] Write test: end-to-end with all mocks ‚Äî verifies `main()` calls `analyze_pcap` with correct args\n- [ ] Write test: `--verbose` flag passed through to `analyze_pcap`\n\n## T-10: Sample PCAP generation script\n\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/generate_sample.py` script using `scapy.all` (`IP`, `TCP`, `UDP`, `ICMP`, `wrpcap`, `Ether`)\n- [ ] Generate 100 packets with mixed protocols (TCP/UDP/ICMP), random IPs, staggered timestamps\n- [ ] Output `sample_traffic.pcap` (< 1MB) to current directory\n- [ ] Run script to produce `examples/pcap_analyzer/sample_traffic.pcap`\n- [ ] Write test: generated PCAP file exists and is < 1MB\n- [ ] Write test: generated PCAP contains at least TCP, UDP, and ICMP packets\n\n## T-11: `README.md` documentation\n\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` with:\n  - Prerequisites (Python 3.10+, `agentcube-sdk`, `ROUTER_URL`)\n  - Quick Start command\n  - Analysis features list (protocol distribution, top IPs, timeline, tshark)\n  - CLI arguments table\n  - Expected output example\n  - Output format description (JSON + stdout summary)\n\n## T-12: Integration tests ‚Äî mocked SDK workflow\n\n- [ ] Write integration test: full workflow with `unittest.mock.patch` on `CodeInterpreterClient`\n  - Verify `upload_file` called with correct paths\n  - Verify `run_code` called for scapy check and analysis\n  - Verify result JSON written to output file\n  - Verify `print_analysis_summary` called\n- [ ] Write integration test: empty PCAP handling (mock returns 0 packets)\n- [ ] Write integration test: `CommandExecutionError` during analysis ‚Üí proper error handling\n\n## T-13: Lint, type-check, and manual verification\n\n- [ ] `python -m py_compile examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` ‚Äî no syntax errors\n- [ ] `python -m py_compile examples/pcap_analyzer/generate_sample.py` ‚Äî no syntax errors\n- [ ] `pytest examples/pcap_analyzer/tests/ -v` ‚Äî all tests pass\n- [ ] Manual E2E: run `python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap` against real AgentCube platform (if available)\n- [ ] Verify `analysis_result.json` output matches design spec JSON schema\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-1 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T-2 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-9\n      ‚îÇ\n      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-3 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n      ‚îÇ\n      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-4 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n      ‚îÇ\n      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-5 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n      ‚îÇ\n      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-6 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n      ‚îÇ\n      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-7 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n      ‚îÇ\n      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-10\n      ‚îÇ\n      ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ T-11\n\nT-8 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-12\n\nT-12 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-13\nT-10 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-13\nT-11 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-13\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T-1 | None |\n| G2 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6, T-7, T-10, T-11 | T-1 |\n| G3 | T-8 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6, T-7 |\n| G4 | T-9 | T-2, T-8 |\n| G5 | T-12 | T-8 |\n| G6 | T-13 | T-9, T-10, T-11, T-12 |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py\">\nERROR [11:6] Import \"langchain_openai\" could not be resolved\nERROR [12:6] Import \"langgraph.prebuilt\" could not be resolved\nERROR [47:18] Import \"agentcube.code_interpreter\" could not be resolved\nERROR [58:25] \"upload_file\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [69:25] \"upload_file\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [78:34] \"execute_command\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_pcap_analyzer.py\">\nERROR [35:6] Import \"example.pcap_analyzer.pcap_analyzer\" could not be resolved\nERROR [169:16] Import \"example.p