{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885027655,"sessionID":"ses_28504be3fffeAI67laka6We2j7","part":{"id":"prt_d7aff051f00178gSn4Pje3z6iP","messageID":"msg_d7afef3a0001vNH6DAKJuxSQO1","sessionID":"ses_28504be3fffeAI67laka6We2j7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a8068ba46c9c4918ae8f16cc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP ÂàÜÊûêÂô®Á§∫‰æãÂ∫îÁî® ‚Äî Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `example` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n4: **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n5: **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## T-1: Project scaffolding ‚Äî `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory structure\n10: \n11: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory\n12: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/__init__.py` (empty, marks package)\n13: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/requirements.txt` with `agentcube-sdk` and `scapy`\n14: - [ ] Verify directory structure matches design spec\n15: \n16: ## T-2: CLI argument parser (`argparse`)\n17: \n18: - [ ] Implement `parse_args()` function with arguments:\n19:   - `--pcap-file` (str, default `sample_traffic.pcap`)\n20:   - `--output` (str, default `analysis_result.json`)\n21:   - `--top-n` (int, default `10`)\n22:   - `--timeline-interval` (float, default `10.0`)\n23:   - `--verbose` (flag, default `False`)\n24: - [ ] Validate `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set; print error and `sys.exit(1)` if missing\n25: - [ ] Write test: all arguments parsed with defaults\n26: - [ ] Write test: explicit arguments override defaults\n27: - [ ] Write test: missing `ROUTER_URL` ‚Üí error message to stderr, exit code 1\n28: \n29: ## T-3: Pre-flight validation helpers\n30: \n31: - [ ] Implement `validate_pcap_file(pcap_file: str) -> None` ‚Äî raises `FileNotFoundError` if file does not exist\n32: - [ ] Implement `check_python_version() -> None` ‚Äî verifies Python 3.10+ via `sys.version_info`\n33: - [ ] Write test: valid PCAP path passes validation\n34: - [ ] Write test: nonexistent PCAP path raises `FileNotFoundError` with descriptive message\n35: - [ ] Write test: Python < 3.10 raises error\n36: \n37: ## T-4: Embedded analysis script (`ANALYSIS_SCRIPT`)\n38: \n39: - [ ] Define `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` constant ‚Äî Python string using `scapy.all` (`rdpcap`, `IP`, `TCP`, `UDP`, `ICMP`, `DNS`, `Raw`)\n40: - [ ] Implement `analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n, timeline_interval)` function inside the script:\n41:   - Parse packets with `rdpcap`\n42:   - Calculate `duration_seconds` from first/last packet timestamps\n43:   - Count protocol distribution (TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, HTTP via `Raw` layer)\n44:   - Compute top N source/destination IPs using `collections.Counter`\n45:   - Build timeline buckets grouped by `timeline_interval`\n46:   - Return JSON-serializable dict matching design spec format\n47: - [ ] Handle empty PCAP (0 packets) gracefully ‚Äî return result with zero counts\n48: - [ ] Write test: embedded script syntax compiles (`py_compile`)\n49: - [ ] Write test: run embedded script locally against a test PCAP, verify JSON structure has all required keys\n50: \n51: ## T-5: `check_tshark_available` helper\n52: \n53: - [ ] Implement `check_tshark_available(client: CodeInterpreterClient) -> bool`\n54: - [ ] Use `client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")` ‚Äî return `True` if non-empty output, `False` on exception\n55: - [ ] Write test: mocked client returns `True` when `which tshark` succeeds\n56: - [ ] Write test: mocked client returns `False` when command raises exception\n57: \n58: ## T-6: `run_tshark_filter` helper\n59: \n60: - [ ] Implement `run_tshark_filter(client, pcap_path, filter_expr) -> str`\n61: - [ ] Construct command: `tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len`\n62: - [ ] Return `client.execute_command(cmd)` output\n63: - [ ] Write test: mocked client returns tshark output string\n64: \n65: ## T-7: `print_analysis_summary` output formatter\n66: \n67: - [ ] Implement `print_analysis_summary(result: dict) -> None` that prints:\n68:   - Header: \"PCAP Analysis Complete\" with separator\n69:   - File name, total packets, duration\n70:   - Protocol distribution with counts and percentages\n71:   - Top N source IPs with packet counts\n72:   - Top N destination IPs with packet counts\n73:   - Result file path\n74: - [ ] Write test: captures stdout, verifies formatted output contains all sections\n75: - [ ] Write test: handles empty protocols dict gracefully\n76: \n77: ## T-8: Core `analyze_pcap` orchestration function\n78: \n79: - [ ] Implement `analyze_pcap(pcap_file, output_file, top_n, timeline_interval, verbose, router_url) -> None`:\n80:   1. Validate PCAP file exists locally\n81:   2. Enter `CodeInterpreterClient` context manager with `name=\"pcap-analyzer\"`, `router_url`, `verbose`\n82:   3. Upload PCAP: `client.upload_file(pcap_file, f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\")`\n83:   4. Best-effort scapy install: try `import scapy`, fall back to `pip install scapy` via `run_code`\n84:   5. Execute analysis: `client.run_code(\"python\", ANALYSIS_SCRIPT)` with parameters\n85:   6. Parse JSON result from `run_code` output\n86:   7. If `check_tshark_available(client)`, run `run_tshark_filter` and attach to result\n87:   8. Write result JSON to `output_file` locally\n88:   9. Call `print_analysis_summary(result)`\n89: - [ ] Wrap in try/except ‚Äî print `Analysis failed: {e}` to stderr, `sys.exit(1)` on failure\n90: - [ ] Write test: mocked `CodeInterpreterClient` verifies full call sequence (upload ‚Üí run_code scapy check ‚Üí run_code analysis ‚Üí file write ‚Üí summary)\n91: - [ ] Write test: scapy already installed skips `pip install`\n92: - [ ] Write test: scapy not installed triggers `pip install`\n93: - [ ] Write test: tshark available ‚Üí additional `execute_command` and `run_tshark_filter` called\n94: - [ ] Write test: tshark not available ‚Üí skips tshark steps\n95: - [ ] Write test: `run_code` raises exception ‚Üí error printed, exit 1\n96: - [ ] Write test: context manager `__exit__` called even on exception (cleanup guarantee)\n97: \n98: ## T-9: `main()` entry point\n99: \n100: - [ ] Implement `main()` function:\n101:   - Call `parse_args()` to get CLI arguments\n102:   - Resolve `ROUTER_URL` from environment\n103:   - Call `analyze_pcap()` with parsed args and router URL\n104: - [ ] Add `if __name__ == \"__main__\": main()` guard\n105: - [ ] Write test: end-to-end with all mocks ‚Äî verifies `main()` calls `analyze_pcap` with correct args\n106: - [ ] Write test: `--verbose` flag passed through to `analyze_pcap`\n107: \n108: ## T-10: Sample PCAP generation script\n109: \n110: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/generate_sample.py` script using `scapy.all` (`IP`, `TCP`, `UDP`, `ICMP`, `wrpcap`, `Ether`)\n111: - [ ] Generate 100 packets with mixed protocols (TCP/UDP/ICMP), random IPs, staggered timestamps\n112: - [ ] Output `sample_traffic.pcap` (< 1MB) to current directory\n113: - [ ] Run script to produce `examples/pcap_analyzer/sample_traffic.pcap`\n114: - [ ] Write test: generated PCAP file exists and is < 1MB\n115: - [ ] Write test: generated PCAP contains at least TCP, UDP, and ICMP packets\n116: \n117: ## T-11: `README.md` documentation\n118: \n119: - [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` with:\n120:   - Prerequisites (Python 3.10+, `agentcube-sdk`, `ROUTER_URL`)\n121:   - Quick Start command\n122:   - Analysis features list (protocol distribution, top IPs, timeline, tshark)\n123:   - CLI arguments table\n124:   - Expected output example\n125:   - Output format description (JSON + stdout summary)\n126: \n127: ## T-12: Integration tests ‚Äî mocked SDK workflow\n128: \n129: - [ ] Write integration test: full workflow with `unittest.mock.patch` on `CodeInterpreterClient`\n130:   - Verify `upload_file` called with correct paths\n131:   - Verify `run_code` called for scapy check and analysis\n132:   - Verify result JSON written to output file\n133:   - Verify `print_analysis_summary` called\n134: - [ ] Write integration test: empty PCAP handling (mock returns 0 packets)\n135: - [ ] Write integration test: `CommandExecutionError` during analysis ‚Üí proper error handling\n136: \n137: ## T-13: Lint, type-check, and manual verification\n138: \n139: - [ ] `python -m py_compile examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` ‚Äî no syntax errors\n140: - [ ] `python -m py_compile examples/pcap_analyzer/generate_sample.py` ‚Äî no syntax errors\n141: - [ ] `pytest examples/pcap_analyzer/tests/ -v` ‚Äî all tests pass\n142: - [ ] Manual E2E: run `python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap` against real AgentCube platform (if available)\n143: - [ ] Verify `analysis_result.json` output matches design spec JSON schema\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Dependency Graph\n148: \n149: ```\n150: T-1 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ T-2 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-9\n151:       ‚îÇ\n152:       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-3 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n153:       ‚îÇ\n154:       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-4 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n155:       ‚îÇ\n156:       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-5 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n157:       ‚îÇ\n158:       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-6 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n159:       ‚îÇ\n160:       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-7 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-8\n161:       ‚îÇ\n162:       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ T-10\n163:       ‚îÇ\n164:       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ T-11\n165: \n166: T-8 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-12\n167: \n168: T-12 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-13\n169: T-10 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-13\n170: T-11 ‚îÄ‚îÄ T-13\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ## Parallelizable Groups\n174: \n175: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n176: |-------|-------|---------------|\n177: | G1 | T-1 | None |\n178: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6, T-7, T-10, T-11 | T-1 |\n179: | G3 | T-8 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6, T-7 |\n180: | G4 | T-9 | T-2, T-8 |\n181: | G5 | T-12 | T-8 |\n182: | G6 | T-13 | T-9, T-10, T-11, T-12 |\n\n(End of file - total 182 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP ÂàÜÊûêÂô®Á§∫‰æãÂ∫îÁî® ‚Äî Tasks\n\n**Module:** `example` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n**Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n\n---\n\n## T-1: Project scaffolding ‚Äî `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory structure\n\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/` directory\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/__init__.py` (empty, marks package)\n- [ ] Create `examples/pcap_analyzer/requirements.txt` with `agentcube-sdk` and `scapy`\n- [ ] Verify directory structure matches design spec\n\n## T-2: CLI argument parser (`argparse`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `parse_args()` function with arguments:\n  - `--pcap-file` (str, default `sample_traffic.pcap`)\n  - `--output` (str, default `analysis_result.json`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775885027646,"end":1775885027653}}}}
